# Day 01 - Maximum Subarray

## Problem Statement
Given an integer array `nums`, find the contiguous subarray that has the largest sum and return its sum.

## Code

class Solution {
public:
    int maxSubArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int currSum = 0, maxSum = INT_MIN;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            currSum += nums[i];

            maxSum = max(currSum, maxSum);

            if(currSum < 0){
                currSum = 0;
            }
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
};


## Time Complexity
**O(n)**

## Space Complexity
**O(1)**

## Approach
This solution uses **Kadane's Algorithm** to find the maximum subarray sum efficiently. We maintain a running sum (`currSum`) and add each element to it while traversing the array. After every addition, we compare `currSum` with `maxSum` and update `maxSum` if a larger sum is found. If `currSum` becomes negative, it is reset to `0` because a negative sum cannot contribute to a larger subarray in the future. By the end of the traversal, `maxSum` stores the maximum sum of any contiguous subarray.
